  "prompt": "How many lines of code was the initial Instagram?",
  "response": "The initial version of Instagram, which was launched in October 2010, was relatively simple compared to the complex app it has become today. While the exact number of lines of code for the initial version isn\u2019t publicly disclosed, it\u2019s estimated to have been on the order of thousands of lines, not hundreds of thousands.\n\nThe app was built by a small team (primarily Kevin Systrom and Mike Krieger) and focused on core features like photo uploading, filtering, and sharing. It was developed in a matter of weeks, suggesting a relatively compact codebase.\n\nFor comparison, early versions of mobile apps like Instagram often ranged from 10,000 to 50,000 lines of code, depending on their complexity. Instagram's initial simplicity likely placed it on the lower end of that range.",
